Third #🤝community-bounties proposed by @vinco  (and similarly @Nina Ch.  more recently): 

:eco_heart: 🌎 **Eco For Life** 🌍 :eco_heart: 

https://discord.com/channels/768556386404794448/836998394065059930/837000368285810689 
From @vinco  *"Eco for life". The idea of bounty is to try to save other lives: donate blood, help shelters with animals that need food or veterinarian help; buy blankets in the elderly etc…*

https://discord.com/channels/768556386404794448/836998394065059930/845652496541286420 
From @Nina Ch.  *Hi everybody, I was thinking in a contest to encourage people to donate blood as the international blood day is coming and like that we can save lifes.*

This is a pretty open ended challenge. Similar to the previous challenge this is all about helping make the world around you a better place to live. How you choose to do that is up to you!

 **Rules**: 
1️⃣ You must be the one performing the act.
2️⃣  It must be ***well documented ***with pictures or videos.
3️⃣  Show off an :eco: Eco Logo  in the documentation.
4️⃣ Attach a 3-4 sentence description of what you are doing to help, why it’s important to your community and why this cause is meaningful to you.
5️⃣ One prize issued per user :eco_heart: 
 

🏆 **Prize** 🏆 : 
Accepted and verified submissions will be granted between 20-250 :points:  depending on the effort put in, the documentation and the description.

:points: **Will be distributed after the close of the challenge** :points: 


⏰  **Closing Date: May 31 2021 at 12 midnight** ⏰ 

Good Luck and thank you for helping make our world a better place!

Hello ECO community. Today my friends @prontera @Skipper and I visited the Ilyinka shelter for homeless animals.
We bought various sweets and useful things, handed them over to the shelter and walked with the animals of the shelter in the fresh air.

The shelter is very large, there are over 500 abandoned dogs and cats.
Walking through the premises of the shelter, it was very sad to observe how every dog ​​wants to be petted and even just walk outside the cage.

And when you see all this live, you understand how important it is to bring at least a little help to such places and just be with these poor animals, because nobody cares about them in ordinary life.

Huge gratitude to the creators of such shelters, who take every effort to make homeless animals less and less.
All the creators of such places are great heroes, because not every person will dare to carry such a load of moral and financial burden absolutely free of charge.

I urge everyone to visit such places, walk with animals, bring at least a little help and leave donations.

I myself will now visit such shelters more often.

Hello community! My wife has a rare blood type (AB +), so she donates blood from time to time. Basically - for women in labor with AB blood type, because such blood is always available, and in childbirth there is a risk for the mother and child.

This is a family with a very difficult fate. Parents don't care about children. The father is unknown, the mother suffers from mental and alcohol problems, wanders. For some time the children were in an orphanage, now they are being raised by their grandmother.

Our acquaintance was by chance - a few years ago the eldest girl from this family was treating a serious illness, and I and other volunteers brought gifts to the hospital. Unfortunately, this story ended sadly.

Today my grandmother is raising two children, and this is very difficult for her financially. I continue to support her.

Now I have collected a set of seasonal clothes and shoes for them.

Hello,
My name is Ildar and I’m from Moscow (Russia) but for 4 last years I’m located in a small Kazakhstan city near Caspian sea – Aktau. Aktau’s population is only about 200k. There is only one blood centre and lack of donors.  
Previously I thought about becoming a blood donor but haven’t realised this initiative. Today I have become a blood donor first time and I want to thank ECO community for this initiative!!!!!!! This announcement has gave me a good kick to go and do (and not only think about it). I’m really hope that my blood will help somebody. 
And a couple of words about my today’s experience:
Looks like - I’m not the best donor)))) – my weight is about 70 kg and I have low hemoglobin. So basically when they took 450 ml of my blood, my pressure has dropped and they had to dip me with saline and even made caffeine shot. I have spent some time lying on the bed before my pressure has normalised and I’ m confident that “Blood centre” personnel will not be happy to see me next time)))))
But I really happy that I was able to take part in this initiative! I have suggested today to general director to send emails inside our company and to organise the same event for all employees and I’m pretty sure that we will be able to do so! 
I want to suggest everybody to spread this blood donor initiative in their Companies, teammates, families and etc. It will be good example for our children and future generation.
This the first time, please be gentle with me

This is a family-type Orphanage. Such work in our country is taken by people who are very selfless. People with big hearts. Because they have a minimum wage and live very poorly, taking many orphans into their families.

I learned about this family many years ago, and since then I sometimes help them. I know how difficult it is financially for them to gather students for the school year. Now there are 10 schoolchildren in this family.

Today, @cooloNe, me and our son went to visit Little Angels Orphanage in Mendez, Cavite. They opened their doors in early 1998 with 3 babies only, but right now they have 29 neglected and abandoned kids in their care. They accept infants up to 18 years old. We brought for them some rice, groceries, foods, veggies and our son shared some of his toys too. Due to COVID, we were allowed limited interaction with the kids and also limited access to the orphanage cause we were hoping to see where the kids play, eat, sleep and activity area.

Here in the Philippines, children has been banned from going outside for a year now due to pandemic. As a parent/s we feel that these kids were deprived of some precious things in life and that’s why we thought of them in the first place. Right now we have many flourishing animals shelters around, we have many COVID initiatives from all around the world but these kids who are actually locked in these institutions seemed to have been forgotten and a bit neglected by the society. These children are our future so let’s give them some hope, some positivity in their life and help them in our own ways. 🙂

Hi friends!
This weekend I with my friend @OBORTS  visited and donated pet supplies and treats for animal shelter in Pyrohovo (Kyiv, Ukraine) which became the real home for animals where they are cared, treated and maintained.
There are over 1600 dogs and 285 cats in the shelter. The number of animals getting to the shelter is increasing. 
I talked to the administration of the shelter and found out that: this shelter exists only due to citizens’ donations. Unfortunately, the financial situation of the citizens is getting worse, consequently the situation of the animals in the shelter as well. So help is needed. There are lots of reasons you might have extra supplies and items around the house that this and other animal shelters might need. Right now is as good a time as any to do some cleaning and do a good deed at the same time.
Take some time to do inventory around your house and see if you have anything you’re ready to get rid of that a shelter might use. It won’t cost you anything to donate the items that you’re getting rid of anyway, you’ll have a cleaner and more organized living space, and you’ll be helping dogs as they wait for their forever homes. Of course any amount cash donation large or small can make the difference in the life of animals as well.
Please consider a donation to your local animal shelter and encourage friends and relatives to do the same.
